### Configure Astro for Server-Side Rendering with Sanity

Source: https://github.com/sanity-io/sanity-astro/blob/main/packages/sanity-astro/README.md

This configuration snippet sets up an Astro project for server-side rendering (SSR) using the Vercel adapter, which is required for Sanity Visual Editing. It also includes the Sanity integration with CDN enabled.

```js
import vercel from '@astrojs/vercel'

// astro.config.mjs
export default defineConfig({
  integrations: [
    sanity({
      useCdn: true,
      // ...
    }),
    // ...
  ],
  output: 'server',
  adapter: vercel(),
})
```

